schemaClass.name: Action
schemaClass.description: An Action entity specifies the mechanism by which inputs are transformed into outputs.

schemaProperty.name: Start
schemaProperty.description: Start represents the time when this Action begins.

schemaProperty.name: Duration
schemaProperty.description: Duration represents the period of time this Action occurs.

schemaProperty.name: Percent Complete
schemaProperty.description: Percent Complete represents the percentage this Action is complete.

schemaClass.name: Artifact
schemaClass.description: An Artifact entity specifies a document or other source of information that is referenced by or generated in the knowledgebase.

schemaProperty.name: Date Published
schemaProperty.description: Date Published represents the date when this Artifact was accessed (webpage), published, or uploaded to the knowledgebase.

schemaProperty.name: File
schemaProperty.description: The File that represents this Artifact.

schemaClass.name: Asset
schemaClass.description: An Asset entity specifies an object, person, or organization that performs Actions, such as a system, subsystem, component, or element.

schemaClass.name: Resource
schemaClass.description: A Resource entity specifies a consumable or producible Asset.

schemaProperty.name: Units
schemaProperty.description: Units represents this Resource's units used to measure the amounts, such as each or tons.

schemaProperty.name: Initial Amount
schemaProperty.description: Initial Amount represents this Resource's starting amount.

schemaProperty.name: Minimum Amount
schemaProperty.description: Minimum Amount represents this Resource's minimum amount allowed.

schemaProperty.name: Maximum Amount
schemaProperty.description: Maximum Amount represents this Resource's maximum amount allowed.

schemaClass.name: Port
schemaClass.description: An interaction point of a block, specifying the input and output flow.

schemaProperty.name: Direction
schemaProperty.description: Direction represents the flow of data on this port.

schemaClass.name: Characteristic
schemaClass.description: A Characteristic entity specifies properties of an entity.

schemaProperty.name: Value
schemaProperty.description: Value represents this Characteristic's current value.

schemaProperty.name: Units
schemaProperty.description: Units represents this Characteristic's units used to measure the value, such as pounds or miles per hour.

schemaClass.name: Measure
schemaClass.description: A Measure entity specifies properties of measurements and measuring methodologies, including metrics.

schemaProperty.name: Projected Value
schemaProperty.description: Projected Value represents this Measure's expected value to be achieved with existing resources.

schemaProperty.name: Threshold Value
schemaProperty.description: Threshold Value represents the minimum acceptable value for this Measure.

schemaProperty.name: Objective Value
schemaProperty.description: Objective Value represents the goal for this Measure.

schemaProperty.name: Improvement Direction
schemaProperty.description: Improvement Direction represents the direction in that metric improvement occurs. It is the direction from the Threshold Value to the Objective Value.

schemaProperty.name: Tolerance
schemaProperty.description: Tolerance represents the percentage of the value that forms the positive and negative tolerance bands. Tolerance is used when Value represents the planned measure value at a given time.

schemaClass.name: Connection
schemaClass.description: A Connection entity specifies the mechanism relating Assets. This is an abstract class.

schemaClass.name: Conduit
schemaClass.description: A Conduit entity specifies the connection between Assets and has capacity and latency, which carries an Input/Output.

schemaProperty.name: Capacity
schemaProperty.description: Capacity represents the maximum rate supported by the Conduit. (Used in simulation as to add time delay by dividing the Input/Output size with the capacity value.)

schemaProperty.name: Latency
schemaProperty.description: Latency represents the time required to transmit the information or Input/Output entity over this Conduit. This value does not factor in any delays due to capacity limitations.

schemaProperty.name: Units
schemaProperty.description: Units represents this Conduit's units used to measure the capacity, such as bits per second or gallons per minute.

schemaClass.name: Logical
schemaClass.description: A Logical entity specifies relationship between Assets. It is primarily used in database schema development and entity-relationship diagrams.

schemaClass.name: Cost
schemaClass.description: A Cost entity specifies the outlay or expenditure (as of effort or sacrifice) made to achieve an objective associated with another entity.

schemaProperty.name: Amount
schemaProperty.description: Amount represents this Cost's value.

schemaProperty.name: Units
schemaProperty.description: Units represents this Cost's units used to measure the amount, such as $ or Euro.

schemaProperty.name: Rate
schemaProperty.description: Rate represents this Cost's billing rate.

schemaProperty.name: Category
schemaProperty.description: Category represents the part of the lifecycle for which the money is used (commonly called Color of Money). This matches the Federal Government (DoD) cost phases.

schemaProperty.name: Contract Type
schemaProperty.description: Contract Type represents this Cost way to identify the reimbursement structure (i.e. CPFF vs T&M).

schemaClass.name: Decision
schemaClass.description: A Decision entity specifies a challenge and its resolution.

schemaProperty.name: Justification
schemaProperty.description: Justification represents the reason and context for making this Decision.

schemaProperty.name: Assumptions
schemaProperty.description: Assumptions represents facts that are used as a basis for this Decision. These assumptions can be taken for granted by the decision maker.

schemaClass.name: Equation
schemaClass.description: An Equation entity specifies an equation (mathematical or logical) that can be used to describe a part of the model.

schemaProperty.name: Value
schemaProperty.description: Value represents this Equation's text.

schemaClass.name: Input/Output
schemaClass.description: An Input/Output entity specifies the information, data, or object input to, triggers, or output from an Action.

schemaProperty.name: Size
schemaProperty.description: Size represents the amount or proportion of this Input/Output, such as 100 as in 100 Gigabytes or number of entities (e.g. 10 as in 10 tokens).

schemaProperty.name: Units
schemaProperty.description: Units represents this Input/Output's units used to measure the size, such as Gigabyte or tokens.

schemaClass.name: Issue
schemaClass.description: An Issue entity specifies a bug, user story, or an epic.

schemaProperty.name: Status
schemaProperty.description: Status represents the current state of this Issue.

schemaProperty.name: Assignee
schemaProperty.description: Assignee represents the user(s) and/or team(s) responsible for the issue.

schemaProperty.name: Priority
schemaProperty.description: Priority represents the level of effect this issue is causing.

schemaClass.name: Location
schemaClass.description: A Location entity specifies where an entity resides.

schemaClass.name: Orbital
schemaClass.description: An Orbital entity specifies a location along an orbit around a celestial body.

schemaProperty.name: Apoapsis
schemaProperty.description: Apoapsis represents the point of greatest distance from the celestial body being orbited. For Earth, the term is apogee. For the Sun the term commonly used is aphelion. The Apoapsis must be specified with the Periapsis to characterize the orbital ellipse shape.

schemaProperty.name: Periapsis
schemaProperty.description: Periapsis represents the point of closest distance from the celestial body being orbited. For Earth, the term is perigee. For the Sun the term commonly used is perihelion. The Periapsis must be specified with the Apoapsis to characterize the orbital ellipse shape.

schemaProperty.name: Eccentricity
schemaProperty.description: Eccentricity represents the amount the orbit deviates from a perfect circle (0 being perfectly circular and 1 is a parabola - no longer a closed orbit). The Eccentricity must be specified with the Semimajor axis to characterize the orbital ellipse shape.

schemaProperty.name: Semimajor Axis
schemaProperty.description: Semimajor Axis represents the one half of the length of the longest diameter of the orbital ellipse. The Semimajor axis must be specified with the Eccentricity to characterize the orbital ellipse shape.

schemaProperty.name: Inclination
schemaProperty.description: Inclination represents the angle between the orbital plane and a reference plane, such as the equatorial plane for Earth. The Inclination must be specified with the Longitude of Ascending Node to characterize the orbital plane.

schemaProperty.name: Reference Plane
schemaProperty.description: Reference Plane represents the reference plane from where the Inclination angle will be calculated.

schemaProperty.name: Longitude of Ascending Node
schemaProperty.description: Longitude of Ascending Node represents the angle from the Origin of Longitude to the ascending node, measured in the Reference Plane. For the Earth, the origin of longitude is typically the Prime Meridian. The Longitude of Ascending Node must be specified with the Inclination to characterize the orbital plane.

schemaProperty.name: Origin of Longitude
schemaProperty.description: Origin of Longitude represents the reference meridian from where the Longitude of Ascending Node will be calculated.

schemaProperty.name: Argument of Periapsis
schemaProperty.description: Argument of Periapsis represents the angle between the Periapsis and the ascending node as measured in the orbital plane in the direction of motion.

schemaProperty.name: Mean Anomaly
schemaProperty.description: Mean Anomaly represents the proportion of orbital area swept since the last Periapsis at the specified time. It is used to define the position of the orbiting Asset along the orbital ellipse.

schemaClass.name: Physical
schemaClass.description: A Physical entity specifies a location on or above the surface.

schemaProperty.name: Address
schemaProperty.description: Address represents this Location's complete address.

schemaProperty.name: Coordinates
schemaProperty.description: Coordinates represents the coordinate points for this Location (GPS or other system).

schemaProperty.name: Altitude
schemaProperty.description: Altitude represents the distance above the surface.

schemaClass.name: Virtual
schemaClass.description: A Virtual entity specifies a location within a digital network.

schemaProperty.name: Address
schemaProperty.description: Address represents the identification address using the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) protocols.

schemaClass.name: Risk
schemaClass.description: A Risk entity specifies the combined probability and consequence in achieving objectives.

schemaProperty.name: Consequence Description
schemaProperty.description: Consequence Description represents the result of this Risk occurring.

schemaProperty.name: Consequence
schemaProperty.description: Consequence represents the level of effect from this Risk occurring.

schemaProperty.name: Probability
schemaProperty.description: Probability represents the chance that this Risk will occur.

schemaProperty.name: Status
schemaProperty.description: Status represents the current state of this Risk.

schemaClass.name: Statement
schemaClass.description: A Statement entity specifies text referenced by the knowledgebase and usually contain in an Artifact.

schemaClass.name: Requirement
schemaClass.description: A Requirement entity identifies a capability, characteristic, or quality factor of a system that must exist for the system to have value and utility to the user.

schemaProperty.name: Rationale
schemaProperty.description: Rationale provides a place to capture the reason(s) behind this Requirement.

schemaProperty.name: Status
schemaProperty.description: Status represents the current state of this Requirement.

schemaProperty.name: Quality Score
schemaProperty.description: The calculated quality score.

schemaProperty.name: Clear
schemaProperty.description: Clear represents if this Requirement is unambiguous and not confusing.

schemaProperty.name: Complete
schemaProperty.description: Complete represents if this Requirement expresses a whole idea.

schemaProperty.name: Consistent
schemaProperty.description: Consistent represents if this Requirement is not in conflict with other requirements.

schemaProperty.name: Correct
schemaProperty.description: Correct represents if this Requirement describes the user's true intent and is legally possible.

schemaProperty.name: Design
schemaProperty.description: Design represents if this Requirement does not impose a specific solution on design; says "what", not "how".

schemaProperty.name: Feasible
schemaProperty.description: Feasible represents if this Requirement is able to be implemented with existing technology, and within cost and schedule.

schemaProperty.name: Modular
schemaProperty.description: Modular represents if this Requirement can be changed without excessive impact on other requirements.

schemaProperty.name: Traceable
schemaProperty.description: Traceable represents if this Requirement is uniquely identified, and able to be tracked to predecessor and successor lifecycle items/objects.

schemaProperty.name: Verifiable
schemaProperty.description: Verifiable represents if this Requirement is provable (within realistic cost and schedule) that the system meets the requirement.

schemaClass.name: Time
schemaClass.description: A Time entity specifies a point or period when something occurs or during which an action, asset, process, or condition exists or continues.

schemaProperty.name: Start

schemaProperty.name: Duration
schemaProperty.description: Duration represents the period of time this Time occurs.

schemaClass.name: Test Case
schemaClass.description: A Test Case entity represents a set of conditions utilized to determine whether a system works as intended.

schemaProperty.name: Set Up
schemaProperty.description: Set Up represents the prerequisites that must be fulfilled before executing this Test Case.

schemaProperty.name: Expected Result
schemaProperty.description: Expected Result represents the result expected when executing this Test Case.

schemaProperty.name: Actual Result
schemaProperty.description: Actual Results represents the results that are captured after executing a Test Case.

schemaProperty.name: Status
schemaProperty.description: Status represents the current state of this Test Case.

schemaClass.name: Transition
schemaClass.description: A Transition entity specifies an action that, once completed, transitions one state (Characteristic) to another state (Characteristic).

schemaClass.name: Task
schemaClass.description: A Task entity specifies an Action that must be completed for a particular project. It served as a "To-Do" for the Project.

schemaClass.name: Dependency
schemaClass.description: A Dependency entity specifies a connection between two Tasks in a Gantt Chart. It defines the relationship a Task depends on another Task in order to Start or Finish

label.name: Independent Verification & Validation Plan Document

label.description: The Test Plan document documents and tracks the necessary information required to effectively define the approach to be used in the testing of the project's product.

label.name: Integrated Logistics Support Plan Document
label.description: The Integrated Logistics Support Plan (ILSP) serves as the master logistics planning document that describes necessary logistic activities, assigns responsibility for those activities, and establishes a schedule for completion.

label.name: Standard Operating Procedure Document
label.description: A Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) is a set of step by step instructions for carrying out a specific technique. They can be used for any technique, but this guide focuses on their use in documenting monitoring techniques, specifically for species and ecological communities.

label.name: Concept of Operations Document
label.description: The Concept of Operations Document (CONOPS) is both an analysis and a formal document that describes how an asset, system, or capability will be employed and supported.

label.name: Requirements Document
label.description: The Requirements Document provides the stakeholders with a clear statement of the capabilities required of the system in order to solve the stakeholder's needs.

label.name: Simulation Output
label.description: Is the dashboard from an executed simulation.

label.name: Project Management Plan Document
label.description: The Project Management Plan (PMP) is a formal document used to document planning assumptions and decisions, facilitate communication among staekholders, and document approved scope, cost, and schedule baslines.
